00:13:08.090 --> 00:13:11.510
a lot of tolerance and tact.

00:13:11.510 --> 00:13:15.770
We always need to work on
feeling like we can bring up

00:13:15.770 --> 00:13:19.880
a challenging situation
and discuss it

00:13:19.880 --> 00:13:21.890
in a non-threatening
way with people.

00:13:21.890 --> 00:13:22.730
JUDITH ORLOFF: Yeah.

00:13:22.730 --> 00:13:24.920
I hope that that's the case.

00:13:24.920 --> 00:13:29.630
Because somebody who is rolling
with being an energy vampire,

00:13:29.630 --> 00:13:31.980
it can really bring down
the work environment.

00:13:31.980 --> 00:13:34.700
So it's really a
toxic influence.

00:13:34.700 --> 00:13:37.460
So I feel that that needs to
be addressed, as you said,

00:13:37.460 --> 00:13:40.420
compassionately and lovingly.

00:13:40.420 --> 00:13:43.820
Because sometimes we don't know
when we get into those states.

00:13:43.820 --> 00:13:45.950
And it could just go
on, and on, and on.

00:13:45.950 --> 00:13:47.960
And you don't want that
in a work environment.

00:13:47.960 --> 00:13:50.450
You optionally want
positive energy

00:13:50.450 --> 00:13:51.530
in your work environment.

00:13:51.530 --> 00:13:54.260
You want it to be easy and
fun so your mind can just

00:13:54.260 --> 00:13:57.950
go to creative places
and really envision

00:13:57.950 --> 00:14:00.230
amazing things for yourself.

00:14:00.230 --> 00:14:02.780
And an energy vampire
is important to identify

00:14:02.780 --> 00:14:05.060
because they could
bring it down.

00:14:05.060 --> 00:14:09.770
And so to address it not
punitively, but lovingly,

00:14:09.770 --> 00:14:12.260
I hope that there is
a way to do that here

00:14:12.260 --> 00:14:15.680
and to recognize not to
get angry at the person,

00:14:15.680 --> 00:14:17.490
but that they need
understanding.

00:14:17.490 --> 00:14:20.060
SPEAKER 1: Not to tell somebody
they're an energy vampire,

00:14:20.060 --> 00:14:20.710
basically.

00:14:24.710 --> 00:14:29.060
So in moving on
with the questions,

00:14:29.060 --> 00:14:32.140
we wanted to ask,
related to that,

00:14:32.140 --> 00:14:37.130
a person who may be
not just in a phase

00:14:37.130 --> 00:14:39.410
in that moment as
an energy vampire,

00:14:39.410 --> 00:14:42.090
but that's their personality.

00:14:42.090 --> 00:14:45.500
They're full on complete
narcissist or something

00:14:45.500 --> 00:14:46.910
lacking.

00:14:46.910 --> 00:14:50.660
Neuroplasticity teaches that
our brain's neural circuitry

00:14:50.660 --> 00:14:51.920
is malleable.

00:14:51.920 --> 00:14:54.920
And studies have shown that
mindfulness meditation, that

00:14:54.920 --> 00:14:57.050
includes loving kindness
that you talked about,

00:14:57.050 --> 00:14:59.090
can rewire the brain.

00:14:59.090 --> 00:15:03.770
So is it possible that
somebody who could possibly

00:15:03.770 --> 00:15:09.890
have a full blown on low empath
narcissist trait, personality,

00:15:09.890 --> 00:15:12.970
change with that?

00:15:12.970 --> 00:15:15.720
JUDITH ORLOFF: It's very hard
for narcissists to change.

00:15:15.720 --> 00:15:17.620
However, I just want
to say, narcissists

00:15:17.620 --> 00:15:19.960
can be really creative,
and productive,

00:15:19.960 --> 00:15:22.520
and have great ideas,
and be very intuitive.

00:15:22.520 --> 00:15:26.600
So they're not all negative
in a work environment.

00:15:26.600 --> 00:15:29.292
It's just the problem
comes in personally,

00:15:29.292 --> 00:15:30.500
where you interact with them.

00:15:30.500 --> 00:15:32.180
Because they just
think of themselves,

00:15:32.180 --> 00:15:34.270
and they don't really
care about what

00:15:34.270 --> 00:15:35.980
you're feeling because
they lack empathy.

00:15:35.980 --> 00:15:39.130
The full blown narcissist,
who are self-absorbed--

00:15:39.130 --> 00:15:41.980
they become cold, withholding,
and punishing when

00:15:41.980 --> 00:15:43.540
you don't do things their way.

00:15:43.540 --> 00:15:47.530
So it doesn't make for a
great management style.

00:15:47.530 --> 00:15:48.710
It really doesn't.

00:15:48.710 --> 00:15:52.600
And so hopefully, there
are not too many here,

00:15:52.600 --> 00:15:55.840
in terms of narcissists, because
it doesn't foster creativity.

00:15:55.840 --> 00:15:56.890
It shuts people off.

00:15:56.890 --> 00:16:00.740
It makes people feel small,
and damaged, and not heard,

00:16:00.740 --> 00:16:01.700
and not listened to.

00:16:01.700 --> 00:16:04.060
And it's so important
if you're sensitive

00:16:04.060 --> 00:16:05.590
and you're an empath--

00:16:05.590 --> 00:16:06.800
you care.

00:16:06.800 --> 00:16:08.870
You really care about others.

00:16:08.870 --> 00:16:10.660
And you don't want
to be shut off.

00:16:10.660 --> 00:16:12.850
But if you do have
narcissists here,

00:16:12.850 --> 00:16:16.180
just take advantage of
all their strengths.

00:16:16.180 --> 00:16:18.460
Nobody's all bad.

00:16:18.460 --> 00:16:21.400
There's a Buddha and a
demon inside everybody.

00:16:21.400 --> 00:16:23.620
It just depends on what we feed.

00:16:23.620 --> 00:16:26.590
We want to feed the best
parts of ourselves, the most

00:16:26.590 --> 00:16:29.800
sensitive, the most loving,
the most compassionate.

00:16:29.800 --> 00:16:32.860
And then understand that we can
be energy vampires sometimes.

00:16:32.860 --> 00:16:36.041
We can go through a bad period.

00:16:36.041 --> 00:16:37.540
So I think with a
narcissist, if you

00:16:37.540 --> 00:16:39.540
look at what they can
give to a work environment

00:16:39.540 --> 00:16:42.220
and not expect them to
be your best friend--

00:16:42.220 --> 00:16:45.460
a lot of patients who come to
me have narcissistic bosses.

00:16:45.460 --> 00:16:47.920
And that's really hard,
because you really

00:16:47.920 --> 00:16:51.700
have to frame things in terms of
how it will serve them for them

00:16:51.700 --> 00:16:53.440
to be on your side.

00:16:53.440 --> 00:16:56.410
And it's tedious,
ego-stroking, and it's

00:16:56.410 --> 00:16:59.120
hard for sensitive people.

00:16:59.120 --> 00:17:01.900
But if you want to have a
vacation, you don't say,

00:17:01.900 --> 00:17:03.110
I'm so tired.

00:17:03.110 --> 00:17:05.016
I really need a break now.

00:17:05.016 --> 00:17:06.099
They won't give it to you.

00:17:06.099 --> 00:17:09.250
But if you say, this
will serve the business.

00:17:09.250 --> 00:17:10.960
Then, a narcissist
will say, oh, OK.

00:17:10.960 --> 00:17:11.710
How?

00:17:11.710 --> 00:17:15.619
And so then it would make more
sense to give you a vacation.

00:17:15.619 --> 00:17:17.599
So ideally, you don't
have to do that,

00:17:17.599 --> 00:17:20.920
but in case you're ever
faced with it, that's

00:17:20.920 --> 00:17:22.369
one tactic that will work.

00:17:25.278 --> 00:17:27.069
SPEAKER 2: I think that
