00:18:21.610 --> 00:18:23.020
SPEAKER 2: Not so many, no.

00:18:23.020 --> 00:18:25.145
JUDITH ORLOFF: Yeah, so
that helps with the feeling

00:18:25.145 --> 00:18:27.190
of spaciousness.

00:18:27.190 --> 00:18:30.160
But in terms of
techniques to use,

00:18:30.160 --> 00:18:32.720
I really suggest meditation.

00:18:32.720 --> 00:18:35.350
There's a three
minute meditation

00:18:35.350 --> 00:18:38.200
where you can just check in
with yourself for three minutes.

00:18:38.200 --> 00:18:41.890
Close your eyes,
focus on your heart,

00:18:41.890 --> 00:18:46.060
focus on something really
positive in your life,

00:18:46.060 --> 00:18:50.410
and breathe out stress,
and focus on the positive.

00:18:50.410 --> 00:18:54.160
And during those three minutes,
you can recalibrate yourself

00:18:54.160 --> 00:18:55.930
and you could come
back to your center.

00:18:55.930 --> 00:18:57.790
Because part of
the skill of being

00:18:57.790 --> 00:18:59.680
an empath in an
environment is learning

00:18:59.680 --> 00:19:02.320
how to come back when
you start to swirl,

00:19:02.320 --> 00:19:04.900
or when somebody pushes your
button and you're triggered,

00:19:04.900 --> 00:19:06.654
or you're disappointed
by something,

00:19:06.654 --> 00:19:09.070
or if something happens in
your personal life and suddenly

00:19:09.070 --> 00:19:10.550
you go down.

00:19:10.550 --> 00:19:14.470
To recenter yourself through
this three minute quick

00:19:14.470 --> 00:19:17.560
meditation is a
form of coming back

00:19:17.560 --> 00:19:20.590
to you that a lot of people
don't know how to do that.

00:19:20.590 --> 00:19:23.260
Once you swirl, they
just start swirling.

00:19:23.260 --> 00:19:25.510
And so learning how to breathe--

00:19:25.510 --> 00:19:27.580
the breath is very powerful.

00:19:27.580 --> 00:19:30.720
Because the breath-- you
can breathe out stress,

00:19:30.720 --> 00:19:35.710
and you can breathe in
clarity, or calm, peacefulness.

00:19:35.710 --> 00:19:38.290
But to breathe out stress,
the breath actually

00:19:38.290 --> 00:19:42.140
carries the stress out
of you, out of your body,

00:19:42.140 --> 00:19:43.520
which is what you want.

00:19:43.520 --> 00:19:45.880
So these regular
meditation breaks

00:19:45.880 --> 00:19:49.420
I really suggest to
help you feel better,

00:19:49.420 --> 00:19:51.790
and to help you reconnect
with your creativity.

00:19:51.790 --> 00:19:54.940
I keep coming back to
that with this audience,

00:19:54.940 --> 00:19:57.490
that creativity is
so important for you

00:19:57.490 --> 00:20:00.370
to be able to
really play up here.

00:20:00.370 --> 00:20:02.800
And to play and to
feel comfortable,

00:20:02.800 --> 00:20:04.360
you have to be in
a good environment.

00:20:04.360 --> 00:20:06.485
And you mentioned that you
have a close environment

00:20:06.485 --> 00:20:08.590
in some places?

