how that helps us?

00:29:44.050 --> 00:29:47.160
JUDITH ORLOFF: That so
helps us in so many ways.

00:29:47.160 --> 00:29:50.940
To get out in nature and take
your shoes off, and go barefoot

00:29:50.940 --> 00:29:53.580
in the grass, or go
barefoot on the ocean,

00:29:53.580 --> 00:29:56.250
just feel yourself,
what that feels like.

00:29:56.250 --> 00:29:58.230
And just the freedom,
it often reminds

00:29:58.230 --> 00:30:01.500
you of how you were as a child,
if you had the opportunity

00:30:01.500 --> 00:30:03.420
to be in nature as a child.

00:30:03.420 --> 00:30:07.890
And to reclaim that, and
to just go play and feel

00:30:07.890 --> 00:30:11.430
what's coming up, the electron
exchange with the earth--

00:30:11.430 --> 00:30:14.010
I have very strong
feelings about the earth,

00:30:14.010 --> 00:30:17.370
and preserving our
environment, and how

00:30:17.370 --> 00:30:19.830
we connect to our
environment, and how

00:30:19.830 --> 00:30:22.380
our bodies are intimately
connected to the earth.

00:30:22.380 --> 00:30:25.180
So of course, we're going to
feel if the earth is harmed.

00:30:25.180 --> 00:30:27.200
And so the mission
of helping the earth

00:30:27.200 --> 00:30:29.790
needs to be number
one, above all things,

00:30:29.790 --> 00:30:31.200
as far as I'm concerned.

00:30:31.200 --> 00:30:34.710
And it's difficult for
empaths in this day and time

00:30:34.710 --> 00:30:37.290
with the support of the
earth not really being there

00:30:37.290 --> 00:30:38.670
in our social environments.

00:30:38.670 --> 00:30:41.550
It's just devastating
for me when

00:30:41.550 --> 00:30:44.100
I hear about certain
ravages of the earth.

00:30:44.100 --> 00:30:48.150
However, you can
go out and connect.

00:30:48.150 --> 00:30:50.196
People aren't trained
to connect to the earth.

00:30:50.196 --> 00:30:52.320
And if you stay in an office
for too long-- or it's

00:30:52.320 --> 00:30:53.400
not actually an office.

00:30:53.400 --> 00:30:55.150
It's an open air environment.

00:30:55.150 --> 00:30:57.060
But if you stay
closed up too long,

00:30:57.060 --> 00:30:59.340
if you stay at your
computer too long,

00:30:59.340 --> 00:31:02.880
you can get sealed
off from the world.

00:31:02.880 --> 00:31:04.080
And you want to connect.

00:31:04.080 --> 00:31:06.810
You want to take a break from
the computer and your work,

00:31:06.810 --> 00:31:07.500
and go out.

00:31:07.500 --> 00:31:09.330
You're so close
to the beach here.

00:31:09.330 --> 00:31:12.060
You could take a walk
and go down to the ocean,

00:31:12.060 --> 00:31:15.920
see all the seagulls, and
get into your child again.

00:31:15.920 --> 00:31:18.870
I know you're adults,
and you work at Google,

00:31:18.870 --> 00:31:22.080
and you have very
important jobs,

00:31:22.080 --> 00:31:25.080
and you really are playing a
role in bettering the world.

00:31:25.080 --> 00:31:30.120
But it's good to also let
that down and go and play,

00:31:30.120 --> 00:31:30.660
if you can.

00:31:30.660 --> 00:31:32.610
Just go and connect
to the earth.

00:31:32.610 --> 00:31:33.930
And you could lie on the earth.

00:31:33.930 --> 00:31:35.400
You could climb a tree.

00:31:35.400 --> 00:31:38.150
You could meditate by a tree.

00:31:38.150 --> 00:31:40.860
But to have that playfulness
and not-- empaths

00:31:40.860 --> 00:31:43.390
tend to get overly serious.

00:31:43.390 --> 00:31:45.000
And life is short.

00:31:45.000 --> 00:31:47.340
So you don't have
as much playfulness

00:31:47.340 --> 00:31:50.070
as you possibly can, to
remind yourself of that.

00:31:50.070 --> 00:31:52.060
Because you deserve it.

00:31:52.060 --> 00:31:53.970
I kind of live
with the philosophy

00:31:53.970 --> 00:31:56.760
of, this is the day I'm
given, the eternal now.

00:31:56.760 --> 00:31:59.040
And I don't know about
tomorrow, necessarily.

00:31:59.040 --> 00:32:00.630
I know about today.

00:32:00.630 --> 00:32:03.036
And I want to make
it the best possible.

00:32:03.036 --> 00:32:05.160
And that isn't just work,
work, work, all the time,

00:32:05.160 --> 00:32:07.930
though I've always
been a workaholic.

00:32:07.930 --> 00:32:09.660
I've always loved to work.

00:32:09.660 --> 00:32:11.940
When I was a little
girl, my report card--

00:32:11.940 --> 00:32:15.300
the teacher said I need to
take the pressure off myself.

00:32:15.300 --> 00:32:17.580
I'm seven years old.

00:32:17.580 --> 00:32:19.620
My parents didn't give me that.

00:32:19.620 --> 00:32:21.610
I was born that way.

00:32:21.610 --> 00:32:24.450
And so it's important for
me to find the balance,

00:32:24.450 --> 00:32:27.080
because I could get
lost in my writing,

00:32:27.080 --> 00:32:33.780
in patience, and the internet,
going on Google and Googling

00:32:33.780 --> 00:32:36.729
things all the time.

